Closes #256 

```python
class MyInt(Int):
    def make_dynamic_default(self):
        if self.default_value != 0:
            return self.default_value
        else:
            return 10

class A(HasTraits):
    i = MyInt()

class B(A):
    i = MyInt(20)

class C(B):
    @default('i')
    def _i_default(self):
        return 30

a, b, c = A(), B(), C()
print(
    A._trait_default_generators['i'](a),
    B._trait_default_generators['i'](b),
    C._trait_default_generators['i'](c)
)
```
```
10, 20, 30
```

This passes all Traitlets tests however Jupyter crashes because it complains that the `transport` trait of `ipykernel.kernelapp.IPKernelApp` does not exist. This indicates that the Traitlets test suite doesn't cover all dynamic default value generation cases, or that Jupyter is exploiting an untested part of Traitlets.

